 MBOMBELA – Guests at Maskmountain Lodge were held up and robbed of their possessions and their vehicle stolen last night. According to Bossies Community Justice’s Danie Theron, the incident occurred at around 21:00. Two armed suspects entered the cabin and tied up two female guests with boxtape and threw a towel over their heads. The owner of the lodge declined to comment. Hi-Tech Security operations manager Callum Mac Pherson confirmed the incident, and said they had responded to the scene. The men robbed them of jewelry, bank cards, cellphones and money. The suspects fled in the guests’ Kia Picanto. The vehicle was later found by Vehicle Recovery Solutions’ Vlam Els in KaNyamazane. Police spokesman Lt Col Erhard Stroh confirmed that police were investigating the incident.